[ introduction ]

imposter is a standalone viewer for OpenOffice.org Impress presentations.
It is released under the GNU General Public License. A copy of the license
is included in the file 'COPYING'.

[ requirements ]

required:
* gtk 2.4 (http://www.gtk.org)

optional:
* iksemel 1.2 (http://iksemel.jabberstudio.org)
    If iksemel is not available, a built in lite version is used.

[ compile & install ]

./configure
make
make install

You can find detailed information in the file 'INSTALL'.
You may need to become root if you are installing into /usr.
You can use compiled program directly without installation.

[ usage ]

Invoke imposter from shell with:

imposter presentations/my_file.sxi

Alternatively you can launch imposter from shell or your favorite dock or
start menu utility and select the file with File/Open... menu. You can even
drag the file from your file manager and drop into the imposter window.

[ keys ]

space: in full screen mode, shows next text line for animated texts
cursor right, page down: turns next page
cursor left, page up: turn previous page
home: jumps to the first page
end: jumps to the last page
f: switches between window and fullscreen modes
esc: quits from imposter
